269
00:14:18,146 --> 00:14:21,446
keep us conductors really busy.

270
00:14:22,246 --> 00:14:25,846
Excuse me. May I help you?

271
00:14:25,846 --> 00:14:27,346
So, when the bell is rung

272
00:14:27,346 --> 00:14:28,946
and the light of the room turns on,

273
00:14:28,946 --> 00:14:30,846
the conductor comes to the room!

274
00:14:30,846 --> 00:14:33,846
Wow! I'm going to give it a try later on too!

275
00:14:33,846 --> 00:14:36,046
Right now, our priority is to find car number 7 that disappeared!

276
00:14:36,046 --> 00:14:38,846
-Let's go confirm! -Aye!

277
00:14:42,746 --> 00:14:45,646
Ai, are you feeling bad because of your cold?

278
00:14:45,646 --> 00:14:49,046
I'm fine because I drank medicine.

279
00:14:49,046 --> 00:14:51,046
Okay, let's go then!

280
00:14:53,546 --> 00:14:57,946
That man just now resembled that person.

281
00:14:57,946 --> 00:15:00,146
But, that burn...

282
00:15:00,146 --> 00:15:01,746
what's going on?

283
00:15:03,546 --> 00:15:05,146
Car number 7?

284
00:15:05,146 --> 00:15:07,046
Is this really car number 7?

285
00:15:07,046 --> 00:15:08,346
Yeah.

286
00:15:08,346 --> 00:15:11,546
Car number 7 has returned!

287
00:15:11,546 --> 00:15:12,846
But, how?

288
00:15:12,846 --> 00:15:16,146
Let's go back to room B once more then.

289
00:15:16,146 --> 00:15:17,846
Yeah.

290
00:15:22,846 --> 00:15:24,446
I'm going to open the door.

291
00:15:26,446 --> 00:15:27,546
Huh?

292
00:15:28,946 --> 00:15:30,246
You know what...

293
00:15:30,246 --> 00:15:31,546
Is this really...

294
00:15:31,546 --> 00:15:33,946
I said it's car number 8, didn't I?

295
00:15:33,946 --> 00:15:37,946
Go back to your room brat, and stay there!

296
00:15:37,946 --> 00:15:39,446
Just what is going on...

297
00:15:39,446 --> 00:15:42,246
I wonder if that conductor's making a mistake.

298
00:15:42,246 --> 00:15:46,146
Could be... He kind of looked sleepy too, so, you know.

299
00:15:46,146 --> 00:15:48,346
Wait a sec...

300
00:15:48,346 --> 00:15:50,246
If I remember correctly, at first...

301
00:15:57,646 --> 00:15:59,246
That's...

302
00:16:02,246 --> 00:16:03,546
Hey, you.

303
00:16:03,546 --> 00:16:05,546
You know, this room...

304
00:16:05,546 --> 00:16:10,346
is really actually room B of car number 7.

305
00:16:10,346 --> 00:16:11,446
Right?

306
00:16:11,446 --> 00:16:13,346
Like I've been trying to tell you...

307
00:16:13,346 --> 00:16:16,746
You received it too, didn't you, Sonoko?

308
00:16:16,746 --> 00:16:18,946
A card that looks like this.

309
00:16:18,946 --> 00:16:22,246
And you did as was instructed on the card, right?

310
00:16:22,246 --> 00:16:24,546
It told you to change rooms temporarily

311
00:16:24,546 --> 00:16:26,646
with the person playing the role of the victim

312
00:16:26,646 --> 00:16:30,446
in order to confuse the detectives that came to this room.

313
00:16:30,446 --> 00:16:32,446
Am I wrong?

314
00:16:32,446 --> 00:16:34,846
Wow! Just as would be expected of you, Conan!

315
00:16:34,846 --> 00:16:36,346
Correct!

316
00:16:36,346 --> 00:16:39,346
Somebody knocked on the door, and when I opened it,

317
00:16:39,346 --> 00:16:41,146
an envelope was on the floor.

318
00:16:41,146 --> 00:16:44,146
This is what was written on the card.

319
00:16:44,146 --> 00:16:48,346
"Congratulations, you've been chosen as the accomplice!"

320
00:16:48,346 --> 00:16:50,646
The rest is just as you said, Conan.

321
00:16:50,646 --> 00:16:52,046
We were instructed to liven up the deduction quiz

322
00:16:52,046 --> 00:16:54,546
by switching rooms with the person playing

323
00:16:54,546 --> 00:16:57,846
the role of the victim in room B of car number 7!

324
00:16:57,846 --> 00:17:00,446
Angry at me for being correct, eh.

325
00:17:00,446 --> 00:17:02,846
And, I happened to pass by

326
00:17:02,846 --> 00:17:04,946
just when the person playing the role of the victim

327
00:17:04,946 --> 00:17:08,946
was switching rooms with them, so I joined them!

328
00:17:08,946 --> 00:17:11,546
So, I'm sure the person playing the role of the victim

329
00:17:11,546 --> 00:17:14,146
is relaxing in car number 8 now.

330
00:17:14,146 --> 00:17:16,046
Then, where's Pops?

331
00:17:16,046 --> 00:17:18,246
He went to the dining room after being told to do so,

332
00:17:18,246 --> 00:17:20,546
by the person playing the victim!

333
00:17:20,546 --> 00:17:22,346
The dining room?

334
00:17:22,346 --> 00:17:24,046
He was told to wait in the dining room

335
00:17:24,046 --> 00:17:27,046
because they wanted him to play the role of the detective

336
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:29,446
that would act as commentator of this deduction quiz at the end.

337
00:17:29,446 --> 00:17:30,846
Oh...

338
00:17:30,846 --> 00:17:32,246
That's that.

339
00:17:32,246 --> 00:17:34,046
But, I guess it's nice to meet you, for the first time, isn't it?

340
00:17:34,046 --> 00:17:35,446
Huh?

341
00:17:35,446 --> 00:17:37,646
It's you, isn't it? The one called Haibara?

342
00:17:37,646 --> 00:17:39,146
Oh, yeah.

343
00:17:39,146 --> 00:17:43,446
I wanted to talk to you from before.

344
00:17:43,446 --> 00:17:45,946
This person...

345
00:17:45,946 --> 00:17:48,146
Don't tell me that...

346
00:17:48,146 --> 00:17:49,646
It can't be.

347
00:17:49,646 --> 00:17:51,046
Who is it?

348
00:17:54,146 --> 00:17:55,446
What?

349
00:17:55,446 --> 00:17:59,146
I thought somebody was peeking through the door just now.

350
00:17:59,146 --> 00:18:01,446
I guess not.

351
00:18:09,246 --> 00:18:13,046
The food and the wine are exquisite.

352
00:18:18,046 --> 00:18:19,946
Fire burning in the field?

353
00:18:36,246 --> 00:18:39,146
You solved the mystery of the missing corpse?

354
00:18:40,546 --> 00:18:44,146
The deduction quiz this time has not been announced yet.

355
00:18:44,146 --> 00:18:46,646
But, I got a card like this!

356
00:18:46,646 --> 00:18:48,246
We did too.

357
00:18:48,246 --> 00:18:50,046
Let me see.

358
00:18:51,646 --> 00:18:53,246
It looks to be the same as the instruction card

359
00:18:53,246 --> 00:18:55,946
that is usually given out but...

360
00:18:55,946 --> 00:19:00,546
what I was told this time was not this sort of trick.

361
00:19:00,546 --> 00:19:02,946
What on earth is going on?

362
00:19:02,946 --> 00:19:05,046
I guess we have no choice but to go to the room

363
00:19:05,046 --> 00:19:06,646
of the person playing the role of the victim,

364
00:19:06,646 --> 00:19:08,246
who's in car number 8 and ask him!

365
00:19:08,246 --> 00:19:10,246
Before that, I got to go to the restroom!

366
00:19:10,246 --> 00:19:12,846
I've got to go too!

367
00:19:14,946 --> 00:19:16,546
What's up, Haibara?

368
00:19:16,546 --> 00:19:20,046
This train... don't you feel a strange presence?

369
00:19:20,046 --> 00:19:21,946
A murderous-like atmosphere.

370
00:19:21,946 --> 00:19:26,546
Well, that's because you've read too many Christie novels.

371
00:19:27,446 --> 00:19:28,846
That presence

372
00:19:28,846 --> 00:19:31,446
doesn't feel to be just one or two people.

373
00:19:36,046 --> 00:19:39,446
Mr. Noto, may I help you?

374
00:19:39,446 --> 00:19:42,746
Mr. Noto! Mr. Noto?

375
00:19:42,746 --> 00:19:45,746
What is it? I didn't call you!

376
00:19:45,746 --> 00:19:47,246
Huh?

377
00:19:47,246 --> 00:19:49,546
But the bell just rung.

378
00:19:49,546 --> 00:19:51,046
Beats me.

379
00:19:51,046 --> 00:19:53,246
I tell you. You don't come when I call

380
00:19:53,246 --> 00:19:55,546
and yet you come when I don't need you.

381
00:19:55,546 --> 00:19:57,346
Oh, I'm so very sorry.

382
00:19:57,346 --> 00:19:59,646
Oh, I'm fine.

383
00:19:59,646 --> 00:20:01,546
There seems to have been some trouble next door,

384
00:20:01,546 --> 00:20:04,346
but it seems to have been a mistake.

385
00:20:05,446 --> 00:20:07,046
All right.

386
00:20:07,046 --> 00:20:09,146
Oh, yes.

387
00:20:15,046 --> 00:20:16,846
Ms. Idenami.

388
00:20:16,846 --> 00:20:19,246
Hey, do something about it, will you?

389
00:20:19,246 --> 00:20:21,146
Do what?

390
00:20:21,146 --> 00:20:25,246
The sound... I hear strange noises in my room!

391
00:20:25,246 --> 00:20:27,746
Oh.

392
00:20:27,746 --> 00:20:30,146
I don't hear anything.

393
00:20:30,146 --> 00:20:32,146
I heard it a while ago!

394
00:20:32,146 --> 00:20:34,746
Are you implicating that I'm lying?

395
00:20:34,746 --> 00:20:37,346
No, I'd do no such thing.

396
00:20:39,646 --> 00:20:42,246
See, it's this sound. You hear it, don't you?

397
00:20:42,246 --> 00:20:44,346
Yes, ma'am. I think it's probably

398
00:20:44,346 --> 00:20:47,546
a cell phone or the like that someone forgot.

399
00:20:47,546 --> 00:20:50,946
Hey, don't come in! I'll look for it myself!

400
00:20:50,946 --> 00:20:52,746
Oh.

401
00:20:52,746 --> 00:20:54,646
What I really want to say is,

402
00:20:54,646 --> 00:20:58,446
why you didn't find that cell phone before the train started off!

403
00:20:58,446 --> 00:21:01,046
I'm very sorry.

404
00:21:01,046 --> 00:21:04,046
What's up?

405
00:21:04,046 --> 00:21:06,946
Over here! This is our room.

406
00:21:06,946 --> 00:21:09,046
Hey, sir,

407
00:21:09,046 --> 00:21:11,346
the trick's already been figured out.

408
00:21:11,346 --> 00:21:14,446
Come out and explain it, will you?

409
00:21:14,446 --> 00:21:18,746
Don't tell me he fell asleep in our room.

410
00:21:19,446 --> 00:21:21,246
No joke!

411
00:21:21,246 --> 00:21:25,046
Sir! Get up and unlock the chain, will you?

412
00:21:25,046 --> 00:21:26,446
Hey, sir!

413
00:21:26,446 --> 00:21:27,546
What's the matter?

414
00:21:27,546 --> 00:21:30,346
He seems to be napping on the sofa.

415
00:21:30,346 --> 00:21:35,146
He's bleeding from the temple, as if he's dead.

416
00:21:35,146 --> 00:21:38,046
I'll bet it's just another part of the deduction quiz?

417
00:21:38,046 --> 00:21:40,146
Move it, will you?

418
00:21:43,346 --> 00:21:45,746
-The smell of... -Gun powder.

419
00:21:46,346 --> 00:21:48,646
Let's break the door down!

420
00:21:48,946 --> 00:21:51,246
Ready, get set, go!

421
00:21:59,146 --> 00:22:00,646
Wow!

422
00:22:00,646 --> 00:22:02,946
Another deduction quiz?

423
00:22:02,946 --> 00:22:04,846
No.

424
00:22:04,846 --> 00:22:06,346
He's really dead.

425
00:22:06,346 --> 00:22:07,946
Huh?

426
00:22:12,746 --> 00:22:14,646
Moreover, this is...

427
00:22:15,946 --> 00:22:18,146
A locked door murder.

428
00:23:43,746 --> 00:23:47,246
I shall splendidly see through the truth

429
00:23:47,246 --> 00:23:50,046
of this Bell Tree Express murder and solve the case!

430
00:23:50,046 --> 00:23:53,746
I just got word from Vermouth.

431
00:23:53,746 --> 00:23:57,546
She says she confirmed that Sherry's on the train.

432
00:23:57,546 --> 00:23:59,046
What shall I do?

433
00:23:59,046 --> 00:24:01,946
If the Organization is really after me

434
00:24:01,946 --> 00:24:04,546
and is on board this train...

435
00:24:04,546 --> 00:24:06,846
I don't stand a chance.

